messages.content:
Short answer:

- You can’t delete Supabase **personal access tokens (PATs)** with the CLI. The CLI doesn’t have PAT-management commands, so `supabase access-token` isn’t a thing.
- Your page shows an **Adlock injection** (`/adlock/injections/script.js`) and “skeleton” rows. That’s very likely why the “three dots” menus won’t open and why programmatic `.click()` throws a **NotAllowedError** (clipboard/use-gesture gating + blocked scripts).

Here’s the fastest way out:

## 1) Fix the UI so you can click
1. **Disable Adlock/any ad/content blocker** for `supabase.com` (you literally have an Adlock script tag on that page).
2. Hard refresh the tab (Cmd+Shift+R) or open the page in **Incognito** with *no extensions enabled*.
3. If it still spins, try another browser (Edge/Chrome/Firefox).  
   *(The local Keychain items you saw don’t affect the 20-token server limit.)*

## 2) Delete tokens via the API from your browser session (no CLI)
If the UI is still stuck, you can call the same Management API that Studio uses, leveraging your current **logged-in browser session**:

Open DevTools Console on the tokens page and run:

```js
// 1) List all personal access tokens
(async () => {
  const res = await fetch('https://api.supabase.com/v1/personal-access-tokens', {
    credentials: 'include',
  });
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`List failed: ${res.status} ${await res.text()}`);
  const tokens = await res.json();
  console.table(tokens.map(t => ({
    id: t.id, name: t.name, last_used: t.last_used_at, created: t.created_at, expires_at: t.expires_at
  })));
  // Keep the id(s) you want to delete and run the delete call below.
})();
```

Delete one by ID:

```js
// 2) Delete a token by id (replace TOKEN_ID)
(async () => {
  const id = 'TOKEN_ID';
  const res = await fetch(`https://api.supabase.com/v1/personal-access-tokens/${id}`, {
    method: 'DELETE',
    credentials: 'include',
  });
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`Delete failed: ${res.status} ${await res.text()}`);
  console.log('Deleted', id);
})();
```

Notes:
- `credentials: 'include'` sends your Supabase auth cookies to `api.supabase.com` (same parent domain).
- If your session is expired you’ll get 401—refresh/login and retry.
- If CORS or auth still block it, grab any **token API request** from the Network tab and **Copy as cURL**, then change the method to `DELETE` and the URL to the token’s `…/personal-access-tokens/{id}`.

## 3) Update CLI (separate but good to do)
You’re on `2.48.3`; update to `2.54.11+`. It won’t add PAT deletion, but keeps other commands current.

---

### Why your JS `.click()` failed
Browsers only treat programmatic `.click()` as a “user gesture” when it’s called inside a real user event handler. Triggering it from the console isn’t a trusted gesture, so any follow-up that touches the **Clipboard API** (what Studio uses when showing/copying tokens) throws `NotAllowedError`. And your Adlock script likely prevents the Radix dropdown from initializing anyway.

If you want, paste me the output of the listing call above and tell me which `id`s to remove, and I’ll give you the exact delete snippets for those.
